<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,542,963]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,303,686,711]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remaks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[362,410,687,711]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
specimens (
<specimenCount box="[553,577,687,711]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<specimenCount box="[577,594,687,711]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
) of 
<taxonomicName authority="Werner, 1939" authorityName="Werner" authorityYear="1939" box="[643,1125,686,711]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Tmethis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cinerascus" subSpecies="cyanipes">
<emphasis box="[643,965,686,711]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Tmethis cinerascus cyanipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Werner" box="[973,1125,687,711]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refString="Werner, F. (1939) Uber einige Orthopteren aus Iran. Konowia, Zeitschrift fur Systematische Insektenkunde, 17, 125 - 137." type="journal article" year="1939">Werner, 1939</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have not been found in the Museums during this study. 
<bibRefCitation author="Werner" box="[470,634,723,747]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refString="Werner, F. (1939) Uber einige Orthopteren aus Iran. Konowia, Zeitschrift fur Systematische Insektenkunde, 17, 125 - 137." type="journal article" year="1939">Werner (1939)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished it from the other taxa by the light blue hind tibia and the greenish-white hind wings (he consulted to only the paper of 
<bibRefCitation author="Uvarov" box="[875,1030,759,783]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refString="Uvarov, B. P. (1933) Studies in the Iranian Orthoptera II. Some new or less known Acrididae. Trudy Zoologitscheskogo Instituta Akad. Nauk SSSR [= Proc. Zool. Inst. Acad. Sci. USSR], 1933, 187 - 233." type="proceedings paper" year="1933">Uvarov 1933</bibRefCitation>
). These characters agree only with 
<taxonomicName box="[151,372,796,819]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Eremopeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[151,372,796,819]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Eremopeza angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Uvarov" box="[527,695,795,819]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refString="Uvarov, B. P. (1934) Studies in the Orthoptera of Turkey, Iraq and Syria. Eos. Revista Espanola de Entomologia, 10, 21 - 119." type="journal article" year="1934">Uvarov (1934)</bibRefCitation>
, which was not compared in 
<bibRefCitation author="Werner" box="[1022,1188,795,819]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refString="Werner, F. (1939) Uber einige Orthopteren aus Iran. Konowia, Zeitschrift fur Systematische Insektenkunde, 17, 125 - 137." type="journal article" year="1939">Werner (1939)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,542,963]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<bibRefCitation author="Uvarov" box="[199,364,831,855]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refString="Uvarov, B. P. (1934) Studies in the Orthoptera of Turkey, Iraq and Syria. Eos. Revista Espanola de Entomologia, 10, 21 - 119." type="journal article" year="1934">Uvarov (1934)</bibRefCitation>
described this taxon as a subspecies of 
<emphasis box="[803,927,830,855]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName box="[803,924,830,855]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Eremopeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbera">E. gibbera</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but it should be considered a valid species by the shape of body, the very narrow dark band on hind wing and, the absence of apical dark spot, although it has similar hind tibia color with 
<taxonomicName box="[475,593,902,927]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Eremopeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbera">
<emphasis box="[475,593,902,927]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">E. gibbera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[828,945,902,927]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Eremopeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis box="[828,945,902,927]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">E. reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the body shape and the similar shade of blue of tibia, but the wing coloration and the dark band are very different.
</paragraph>
